    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "rebuilding implies there's something left to rebuild. but there isn't. you talk about resilience like it's some magical thing, but it's just staying in a room that's actively collapsing on you. i'm just tired of the noise, the pretending to be okay, the trying to find a \"new path\" when the old one was the only thing that gave me weight. everything feels so heavy and so pointless. it's like i'm just waiting for the lights to go out so i can finally stop the performance. don't you think there's a certain dignity in just acknowledging when a chapter is truly, completely finished?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
